 massive\nnuclear clusters have high escape velocities (300-500 km/s). A future detection\nof a massive BH in the pair-instability mass gap with low spin would therefore\nnot be proof of the existence of primordial BHs, which are sometimes claimed to\nhave low spins and arbitrarily high masses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Feb 2020 08:25:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 23 Aug 2020 07:17:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-02"}
