{"id":"2002.08228","submitter":"Johannes Schleischitz","authors":"Johannes Schleischitz","title":"Cartesian product sets in Diophantine approximation with large Hausdorff\n  dimension","comments":"25 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We find sets naturally arising in Diophantine approximation whose Cartesian\nproducts exceed the expected Hausdorff dimension, that is the sum of the single\ndimensions. We also address their packing dimensions. Examples include $n$-fold\nproducts of the set of Liouville numbers as well as of the Diophantine numbers\nwith prescribed irrationality exponent. In particular, we show that almost\nevery real number with respect to Lebesgue measure can be written as the sum of\ntwo numbers with sufficiently large prescribed irrationality exponents. A\nsimilar result holds when restricting to classical missing digit Cantor sets.\nThis implies that the subset of numbers with prescribed large irrationality\nexponent has full packing dimension, i.e. the same packing dimension as the\nentire Cantor set. This complements results on the Hausdorff dimension of these\nsets, an intensely studied topic. Our proofs extend ideas of Erd\\H{o}s.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Feb 2020 15:09:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Mar 2020 14:03:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 5 Jan 2022 10:20:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-06"}
